claim.claim-text:
13. An apparatus for the application of topical negative pressure therapy to a user of the apparatus, the apparatus comprising:
a device and a waste canister releasably connected thereto;
wherein:
the device and waste canister are connected together by one or more clip members configured to extend between the device and the waste canister;
the clip members are configured to fail in the event of application of an abnormal force to the apparatus; and
the disengagable feature at the device end is an inwardly turned resiliently deformable finger portion on the clip member which engages with a tooth portion on the device.
